 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">In summary, studies reporting evidence of selection for smaller body size are still very sparse, and no overall conclusion can be drawn on the adaptive nature of temporal size trends in the context of climate warming. More importantly, more data are needed to better understand how climatic factors shape selection pressures.</p>
</sec>
